HEADWORD: Nero-antico
<hw>Ne`ro-an*ti"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.;
<ets>nero</ets> black + <ets>antico</ets> ancient.]</ety>
<fld>(Art)</fld> <def>A beautiful black marble found in fragments among
Roman ruins, and usually thought to have come from ancient
Laconia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

